ng> "},{"content":"Transfer dough onto a silicone bread mat or floured work surface and work into a tight ball. Wrap in plastic wrap and place into refrigerator to chill for a minimum 30 minutes."},{"content":"Preheat oven to 180°C. Roll out ⅔ of the pastry between a silicone bread mat and a sheet of baking paper or between two sheets of baking paper into a circle (25 cm)."},{"content":"Line pie dish with rolled out pastry, then place into refrigerator to chill for 15 minutes. Wrap remaining pastry in plastic wrap and place into refrigerator until ready to use."},{"content":"Blind bake pastry case for 20 minutes (180°C) or until lightly golden. Set pastry case aside to cool while you prepare the filling."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Chicken and pear filling"},{"content":"Preheat the oven to 200°C."},{"content":"Place garlic and leek into mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 7<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add butter and sauté <b>3 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add chicken, thyme and pepper and cook <b>5 min\/90°C\/\/speed 1<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Place a ceramic or glass bowl onto mixing bowl lid, then weigh water into it. Add cornflour to ceramic or glass bowl and stir until cornflour has dissolved."},{"content":"Add cornflour and water mixture, stock paste and wine and cook <b>5 min\/90°C\/\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add pear and cook <b>8 min\/90°C\/\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add cream and combine <b>20 sec\/\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Transfer chicken and pear filling into pastry case. Remove remaining pastry from refrigerator, then roll out on a silicone bread mat or floured work surface into a circle (23 cm)."},{"content":"Place pastry circle over pie and seal the edges by pressing down with your fingertips or a fork. Make two slits in the center of the pastry to allow steam to escape, then bake for 40-50 minutes (200°C) or until pastry is golden brown. Serve hot."}],"h